<P class=3DMsoNormal style=3D"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT=20
face=3D"Times New Roman">AI*IA-07 Special Track on "AI for Intelligent =
Access to=20
Multimedia Data"<o:p></o:p></FONT></P>
<P class=3DMsoNormal style=3D"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT=20
face=3D"Times New =
Roman">******************************************************************=
******<o:p></o:p></FONT></P>
<P class=3DMsoNormal style=3D"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><o:p><FONT=20
face=3D"Times New Roman">&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=3DMsoNormal style=3D"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT=20
face=3D"Times New Roman">Description<o:p></o:p></FONT></P>
<P class=3DMsoNormal style=3D"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><o:p><FONT=20
face=3D"Times New Roman">&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=3DMsoNormal style=3D"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=3D"Times =
New Roman">The=20
full exploitation of multimedia archives is only viable through =
technologies=20
that allow filling the so-called Semantic Gap between low-level =
multimedia=20
descriptors and the semantics of human interpretation. =
<o:p></o:p></FONT></P>
<P class=3DMsoNormal style=3D"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT=20
face=3D"Times New Roman">Although technologies for indexing of AV =
material are now=20
available, locating the suitable information given the scale and the=20
heterogeneity of the current and growing archives is still an open =
problem. As=20
the tradition and trends in information retrieval and Web search =
suggests,=20
information integration at a conceptual level and automatic knowledge =
discovery=20
and acquisition are required. The role of AI is here twofold. On one =
side=20
knowledge representation technologies are requested to support the =
managemenet=20
of the overall complexity according to current standard formalisms and =
best=20
practices applied in the Semantic Web. On the other hand, the typical =
redundancy=20
in multimedia data opens the way to intelligent inductive technologies. =
Data=20
mining and machine learning methods can be successfully applied to =
enrich data=20
descriptions, increase their abstraction leveland scale up to the =
suitable=20
dimensions. Mining the huge information and knowledge embodied by the=20
audiovisual archives represents an important step forward.=20
<o:p></o:p></FONT></P>
<P class=3DMsoNormal style=3D"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><o:p><FONT=20
face=3D"Times New Roman">&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=3DMsoNormal style=3D"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=3D"Times =
New Roman">In=20
this special track, researchers and practitioners from academic and =
industrial=20
institutions are expected to present their work in the area of =
multimedia=20
content processing and artificial intelligence. Recent theoretical and=20
applicative results about representation, indexing, acquisition and =
delivery of=20
multimedia semantics in real scenarios will be presented and discussed. =
The=20
outcome will represent a possibly heterogenous but wide picture of the =
area that=20
surveys current results and stimulates cross-fertilization among =
independent=20
research fields. <o:p></o:p></FONT></P>
<P class=3DMsoNormal style=3D"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><o:p><FONT=20
face=3D"Times New Roman">&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>
